class DDSetDebugger: Debugger implementing the DDSET algorithm for abstracting failure-inducing inputs.

__init__(self, grammar: Dict[str, List[Union[str, Tuple[str, Dict[str, Any]]]]], generalizer_class: Type = <class 'TreeGeneralizer'>, parser: Optional[fuzzingbook.Parser.Parser] = None, **kwargs: Any) -> None: Constructor. `grammar` is an input grammar in fuzzingbook format. `generalizer_class` is the tree generalizer class to use (default: `TreeGeneralizer`) `parser` is the parser to use (default: `EarleyParser(grammar)`). All other keyword args are passed to the tree generalizer, notably: `fuzzer` - the fuzzer to use (default: `GrammarFuzzer`), and `log` - enables debugging output if True.
__repr__(self) -> str: Return a string representation of the generalized call.
fuzz(self) -> str: Return a call with arguments randomly instantiated from the abstract failure-inducing pattern.
fuzz_args(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: Return arguments randomly instantiated from the abstract failure-inducing pattern.

generalize(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: Generalize arguments seen. For each function argument, produce an abstract failure-inducing input that characterizes the set of inputs for which the function fails.
__enter__(self) -> Any: Called at begin of `with` block. Turn tracing on.
__exit__(self, exc_tp: Type, exc_value: BaseException, exc_traceback: traceback) -> Optional[bool]: Called at end of `with` block. Turn tracing off.
__init__(self) -> None: Initialize collector
args(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: Return the dictionary of collected arguments.
call(self, new_args: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None) -> Any: Call collected function. If `new_args` is given, override arguments from its {var: value} entries.
exception(self) -> Optional[BaseException]: Return the exception produced, or `None` if none.
function(self) -> Callable: Return the function called.

class TreeGeneralizer: Determine which parts of a derivation tree can be generalized.

__init__(self, grammar: Dict[str, List[Union[str, Tuple[str, Dict[str, Any]]]]], tree: Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]], test: Callable, max_tries_for_generalization: int = 10, **kwargs: Any) -> None: Constructor. `grammar` and `tree` are as in `TreeMutator`. `test` is a function taking a string that either * raises an exception, indicating test failure; * or not, indicating test success. `max_tries_for_generalization` is the number of times an instantiation has to fail before it is generalized.
can_generalize(self, path: List[int], tree: Optional[Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]] = None) -> bool: Return True if the subtree at `path` can be generalized.

find_paths(self, predicate: Callable[[List[int], Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]], bool], path: Optional[List[int]] = None, tree: Optional[Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]] = None) -> List[List[int]]: Return a list of all paths for which `predicate` holds. `predicate` is a function `predicate`(`path`, `tree`), where `path` denotes a subtree in `tree`. If `predicate()` returns True, `path` is included in the returned list.
fuzz_tree(self, tree: Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Return an instantiated copy of `tree`.
generalizable_paths(self) -> List[List[int]]: Return a list of all paths whose subtrees can be generalized.
generalize(self) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Returns a copy of the tree in which all generalizable subtrees are generalized (= replaced by nonterminals without children)

generalize_path(self, path: List[int], tree: Optional[Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]] = None) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Return a copy of the tree in which the subtree at `path` is generalized (= replaced by a nonterminal without children)
test_tree(self, tree: Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]) -> bool: Return True if testing `tree` passes, else False
class TreeMutator: Grammar-based mutations of derivation trees.

__init__(self, grammar: Dict[str, List[Union[str, Tuple[str, Dict[str, Any]]]]], tree: Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]], fuzzer: Optional[fuzzingbook.GrammarFuzzer.GrammarFuzzer] = None, log: Union[bool, int] = False): Constructor. `grammar` is the underlying grammar; `tree` is the tree to work on. `fuzzer` is the grammar fuzzer to use (default: `GrammarFuzzer`)
get_subtree(self, path: List[int], tree: Optional[Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]] = None) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Access a subtree based on `path` (a list of children numbers)
mutate(self, path: List[int], tree: Optional[Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]] = None) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Return a new tree mutated at `path`
new_tree(self, start_symbol: str) -> Tuple[str, Optional[List[Any]]]: Create a new subtree for <start_symbol>.
